    "sa_faq_Bmctzz": {
      "type": "sa-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "tab_PQNFbQ": {
          "type": "tab",
          "settings": {
            "label": "Products Features"
          }
        },
        "qa_zpKQwC": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "1",
            "question": "<p>How do I set up and operate the Yarbo Snow Blower?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Setup takes minutes: draw your driveway once in the app, and Yarbo Snow Blower handles every storm automatically. It monitors weather conditions and begins clearing when snowfall starts—no manual activation needed. The system auto-docks at ~20% battery, recharges to ~80% in 90 minutes, and resumes clearing throughout multi-day storms.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_ndwRL9": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "1",
            "question": "<p>Can I control the Yarbo Snow Blower manually when needed?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. While autonomous operation is the primary mode, you maintain full remote control via smartphone. Adjust throwing distance (6–40 ft), direction (chute rotation -10° to 190°), intake height, and clearing patterns—all from indoors. Switch between scheduled autonomous clearing and manual spot-clearing as needed for custom snow removal.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_cjUCd9": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "1",
            "question": "<p>Is the Yarbo Snow Blower suitable for my driveway type?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Yarbo Snow Blower adapts to various driveway configurations: large two-car driveways (24-inch clearing width covers wide lanes), gravel driveways (raise intake ~2 inches to skim uneven surfaces), circular driveways (Spiral Mode for efficient coverage), and multi-zone properties (map driveways, paths, and sidewalks separately). Yarbo Snow Blower clears up to 6,000 ft² per charge in 1 inch of snow.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_N84fJ9": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "1",
            "question": "<p>How does the Yarbo Snow Blower perform compared to traditional snow blowers?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Yarbo Snow Blower eliminates manual shoveling and operates 24/7 during storms—preventing dangerous buildup that traditional blowers can't match. The 2-stage design handles snow intake up to 12 inches deep, while autonomous operation means you wake up to cleared driveways without lifting a finger. With a 90-minute runtime and 90-minute recharging (20% to 80%), Yarbo Snow Blower enables continuous operation throughout extended storms.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_GxTNfN": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "1",
            "question": "<p>What surfaces can the Yarbo Snow Blower operate on, and how does it handle uneven ground?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Yarbo Snow Blower operates on a wide range of surfaces, including paved driveways, concrete walkways, asphalt, and gravel. The rubber track system adapts to surface irregularities, and the linear actuator raises the auger to navigate small steps and surface imperfections up to 2 inches (5 cm)—such as sidewalk cracks, tile gaps, and uneven transitions. For gravel surfaces, simply raise the intake height to skim above loose stones and prevent debris from being thrown. Yarbo Snow Blower handles slopes up to 36% (21°), making it suitable for sloped driveways and tiered properties.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_3eiKta": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "1",
            "question": "<p>How does the Yarbo Snow Blower handle extreme cold and heavy storm conditions?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Yarbo Snow Blower is engineered for harsh winter environments with an operating range of -13°F to +140°F (-25°C to +60°C) as standard. For extreme conditions down to -40°C, onboard heating modules protect the battery and drivetrain—keeping Yarbo Snow Blower fully operational even in the most severe winter storms. The 2-stage design with 24-inch clearing width and up to 40-foot throwing distance handles dry, wet, and packed snow types. Rather than waiting for snow to accumulate, Yarbo Snow Blower is designed to begin clearing immediately when snowfall starts—preventing dangerous buildup before it becomes unmanageable.</p>"
          }
        },
        "tab_KpdA9K": {
          "type": "tab",
          "settings": {
            "label": "Support & Care"
          }
        },
        "qa_NtAyVa": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "2",
            "question": "<p>I'm having trouble with setup—what should I do?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Follow the step-by-step guide in the Yarbo App or included user manual. For additional help, visit wiki.yarbo.com, join our Discord Forum, or connect with users in our Official Facebook Group. Reach 24/7 support at 1 (631) 818-1850, email <a href=\"mailto:support@yarbo.com\">support@yarbo.com</a>, or submit a ticket through the Yarbo App.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_Fxi3gm": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "2",
            "question": "<p>What is Yarbo’s return policy?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Yarbo offers a <strong>30-day return policy</strong> for eligible products.To qualify for a return:</p><ul><li> The product must be in <strong>original packaging</strong></li><li> All accessories and documentation must be included </li><li> The item must be in <strong>resalable condition</strong></li></ul><p>Return shipping fees and packaging costs may be deducted if applicable.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_BzVJqQ": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "2",
            "question": "<p>What warranty does Yarbo offer?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Yarbo products include a <strong>2-year limited warranty</strong>.You can also choose an <strong>optional 3-year extended warranty</strong>, providing up to <strong>5 years of total coverage</strong> (available in select regions).</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_4JVn4r": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "2",
            "question": "<p>Can I cancel my order after placing it?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Yes—orders can be canceled before shipment.<br/>If the order has already shipped, it will be treated as a return and subject to the return policy.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_7xFHi6": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "2",
            "question": "<p>What if my delivery is delayed?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>While Yarbo aims for fast delivery, delays may occur due to:</p><ul><li> Weather conditions </li><li> Carrier issues </li><li> High seasonal demand </li></ul><p>Yarbo will keep you updated with tracking and support assistance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_CtmjmK": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "2",
            "question": "<p>How can I contact Yarbo support?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>You can reach Yarbo through:</p><ul><li> Email: <strong>support@yarbo.com</strong></li><li> Phone: <strong>+1 (631) 818-1850</strong></li><li> Yarbo App support system </li></ul><p>Support is available <strong>24/7</strong>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "qa_mwpTc8": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "tab": "2",
            "question": "<p>How long does Yarbo shipping take?</p>",
            "answer": "<p>Yarbo orders typically ship within <strong>3–8 business days</strong> for in-stock products in the United States.<br/> For <strong>pre-order items</strong>, delivery timelines are shown on the product page.For <strong>Canada and Europe</strong>:</p><ul><li> Core & Modules: 3–8 business days </li><li> Accessories: 10–15 business days </li></ul>"
          }
        }
